International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Thu 2 May 2019
Source: OIE, WAHID [edited]
http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapFullEventReport&reportid=30353


African swine fever [ASF], Hungary
-------------------------
Information received on [and dated] 2 May 2019 from Dr Lajos Bognar, deputy state secretary chief veterinary officer, Food Chain Safety Department, Ministry of Agriculture, Budapest, Hungary

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 28 Apr 2019
Date of confirmation of the event: 29 Apr 2019
Reason for notification: 1st occurrence of a listed disease
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: African swine fever virus
Nature of diagnosis: laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country.

New outbreaks (2)
Outbreak 1: Almosd, Hajdu-Bihar
Date of start of the outbreak: 28 Apr 2019
Outbreak status: resolved on 29 Apr 2019
Epidemiological unit: forest
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered
Wild boar: _Sus scrofa_ (Suidae) / - / 1 / 1 / 0 / 0

Outbreak 2: Nyirabrany, Hajdu-Bihar
Date of start of the outbreak: 28 Apr 2019
Outbreak status: resolved on 29 Apr 2019
Epidemiological unit: forest
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered
Wild boar: _Sus scrofa_ (Suidae) / - / 2 / 2 / 0 / 0

Summary of outbreaks:
Total outbreaks: 2
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered
Wild boar: _Sus scrofa_ (Suidae) / - / 3 / 3 / 0 / 0
Outbreak statistics [rates apparent, expressed as percentages]
Species / Morbidity rate / Mortality rate / Case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Wild boar: _Sus scrofa_ (Suidae) / ** / ** / 100 / **
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and/or slaughter
**Not calculated because of missing information

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive

Control measures
Measures applied: movement control inside the country; surveillance outside containment and/or protection zone; surveillance within containment and/or protection zone; traceability; official disposal of carcasses, by-products, and waste; control of wildlife reservoirs; zoning; disinfection; vaccination permitted (if a vaccine exists); no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: no other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
Veterinary Diagnostic Directorate (national laboratory) / wild boar / real-time PCR / 29 Apr 2019 / positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

[The location of the outbreaks can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.]

